<title>PORTUGAL: Portuguese firms may repay state over 120 bln esc.</title>
<headline>Portuguese firms may repay state over 120 bln esc.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-01-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Portuguese companies could repay more than 120 billion escudos in arrears to the tax and social security system under the so-called &quot;Mateus Plan,&quot; Prime Minister Antonio Guterres said.</p>
<p>The &quot;Mateus Plan&quot;, named after Economy Minister Augusto Mateus, gives incentives to companies in financial difficulties to repay arrears to the tax and social security authorities before a January 31 deadline.</p>
<p>Asked if the government could double by that deadline the 60 billion escudos already repaid to the state, Guterres told reporters: &quot;The figure could be higher (than that).&quot;</p>
<p>-- Fernanda Pargana, Lisbon newsroom +351-1-3538254</p>
